        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Maintenance schedules per vehicle</td><td>Paper logs, sticky notes, "it was due 3,000 miles ago"</td></tr>
          <tr><td>DOT/company inspection checklists</td><td>Pre-trip forms that get lost or filled out after the fact</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Fuel & mileage tracking</td><td>Receipt shoebox, fuel card statements, manual mileage logs</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Repair & service history</td><td>The mechanic's invoice you filed somewhere</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Driver assignment & scheduling</td><td>Whiteboard schedules, group chat coordination</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Alerts & notifications</td><td>"I forgot to tell you the oil light was on"</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Step 1: Create Your Account and Add Vehicles</h2>
      <p>Navigate to FleetSafe Pro and create an account with your business email. The onboarding screen asks for your company name, fleet size, and primary trade type — this tailors the inspection templates and maintenance intervals to your industry.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Enter vehicle details:</strong> Make, model, year, VIN, license plate, and assigned driver for each truck or van in your fleet</li>
        <li><strong>Set maintenance intervals:</strong> Oil changes every 5,000 miles, tire rotations every 10,000 miles, brake inspections every 20,000 miles — the system will track mileage and alert you when each service is due</li>
        <li><strong>Upload registration & insurance docs:</strong> Store digital copies in each vehicle's profile so drivers can access them from the field during a traffic stop or accident</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Add all vehicles now. Even the ones that are currently out of service. FleetSafe Pro can log downtime reasons and help you decide whether to repair or replace later.</p>

      <h2>Step 2: Configure Inspection Checklists</h2>
      <p>FleetSafe Pro comes with pre-built inspection templates for standard DOT-compliant pre-trip and post-trip checks. You can customize these for your specific fleet. A typical pre-trip inspection checklist includes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Exterior walkaround:</strong> Lights, tires (tread depth + pressure), mirrors, windshield, body damage</li>
        <li><strong>Under hood:</strong> Oil level, coolant level, brake fluid, power steering fluid, belt condition</li>
        <li><strong>Cabin check:</strong> Seat belts, horn, wipers, defroster, emergency kit, fire extinguisher</li>
        <li><strong>Paperwork:</strong> Registration, insurance card, inspection sticker current</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Each checklist item can be marked Pass, Fail, or N/A. Failed items prompt a required repair note and auto-notify the fleet manager. This creates a defensible maintenance record — critical for insurance claims, lease returns, and DOT audits.</p>

      <h2>Step 3: Assign Drivers and Set Permissions</h2>
      <p>Each vehicle in FleetSafe Pro gets assigned to a primary driver. Every driver receives a login link and can complete inspections, log fuel, and report issues from their phone. The web dashboard is designed for field use — no app download required if drivers prefer mobile web.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Driver permissions:</strong> Can submit inspections, log fuel, and flag issues. Cannot edit maintenance schedules or remove vehicles</li>
        <li><strong>Manager permissions:</strong> Full access — approve repairs, adjust intervals, view fleet-wide analytics, export compliance reports</li>
        <li><strong>Owner permissions:</strong> Billing, user management, data export, and integrations with other platforms like <a href="/tradequote/">TradeQuote Pro</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p>Send drivers their invite links during the weekly team meeting. The setup per driver takes 90 seconds — enter email, assign vehicle, set permission level.</p>

