      <h2>Step 4: Start Logging Fuel and Mileage</h2>
      <p>Fuel costs are the second-largest operating expense for contractor fleets after labor. FleetSafe Pro lets drivers log fuel purchases at the pump — odometer reading, gallons, price per gallon, and total cost. The receipt can be photographed and attached directly to the log entry.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Per-vehicle fuel economy:</strong> The dashboard calculates MPG automatically from odometer + fuel volume entries. A truck that drops below its baseline MPG triggers an alert — early sign of engine trouble</li>
        <li><strong>Monthly fuel cost reports:</strong> Exportable by vehicle, driver, or route type. Compare fuel spend across the fleet to identify which trucks are inefficient</li>
        <li><strong>Mileage tracking for job costing:</strong> Link mileage entries to specific jobs so you can factor transportation cost into your job profitability reports in <a href="/tradequote/">TradeQuote Pro</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p>Drivers can log fuel in under 20 seconds at the pump. The data accumulates into a year-round cost picture that makes tax season, DOT reporting, and fleet budgeting much simpler.</p>

      <h2>Step 5: Set Up Maintenance Alerts and Scheduling</h2>
      <p>This is the core feature that prevents breakdowns. FleetSafe Pro tracks two maintenance triggers: odometer-based (every X miles) and calendar-based (every X months). When a vehicle crosses a threshold, the system sends an alert to both the driver and the fleet manager.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Odometer-based alerts:</strong> Oil change due in 500 miles, tire rotation at 45,000 miles, transmission service at 60,000 miles</li>
        <li><strong>Calendar-based alerts:</strong> Annual state inspection due next month, registration renewal, insurance policy expiry</li>
        <li><strong>Repair scheduling:</strong> When a driver flags an issue during a pre-trip inspection, the system can generate a work order and send it to your preferred mechanic or shop</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Contractors who enable all three alert layers report an average of 80% fewer roadside breakdowns within the first quarter. Preventive maintenance costs pennies compared to emergency repair plus lost job revenue.</p>

      <h2>Step 6: Review Fleet Health Reports Weekly</h2>
      <p>FleetSafe Pro generates a weekly fleet health summary that every contractor should review on Monday morning. The report shows:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Vehicles due for service this week</strong> — schedule them before they fail</li>
        <li><strong>Outstanding inspection failures</strong> — issues flagged but not yet repaired</li>
        <li><strong>Fuel efficiency trends</strong> — vehicles that are underperforming</li>
        <li><strong>Cost per mile</strong> — fuel + maintenance divided by total miles driven</li>
      </ul>
      <p>A 10-minute Monday review of this report keeps the entire fleet running at peak efficiency. Pair it with your weekly job schedule from <a href="/tradequote/">TradeQuote Pro</a> to ensure every job has a truck assigned and the truck is confirmed road-ready.</p>

